Audrey Harrer is an alt-chamber composer/vocalist/harpist who explores sound, language, and aesthetic in relationship to meaning. Her music is an eccentric blend of nostalgic vocals, cinematic imagery, and playful dissonance. Audrey looks for clever ways to connect lyric and gesture and is particularly interested in the space where music and drama collide.

Her solo set is a combination of vocal gymnastics, live looping and processed harp. crispinswank.com
Crispin Swank is a singer, guitarist, and songwriter from just east of the prairie. He picked up a guitar at 13 years-old and carried it with him to Oberlin College and Conservatory, where he worked with Stephen Aron to develop strong classical technique and with new music composers and compositions to nurture his curious look at the guitar. Crispin writes songs to fill in the chasms of consciousness that elude conventional description. He draws listeners closer to the frontier of possible interpretations with twists and turns of harmony, word, and endless streams of melody. He seeks the frayed edges of meanings and feelings to offer musical remedy to other wanderers.
